.TH "drm_connector_set_vrr_capable_property" 9 "drm_connector_set_vrr_capable_property" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_connector_set_vrr_capable_property \- sets the variable refresh rate capable property for a connector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_connector_set_vrr_capable_property
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "bool capable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
drm connector
.IP "capable" 12
True if the connector is variable refresh rate capable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Should be used by atomic drivers to update the indicated support for
variable refresh rate over a connector.
